From: Daniel Micay <danielmicay@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 15 May 2017 23:51:12 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 068/103] sanity check for negative length in nla_memcpy

Extracted from PaX.

Signed-off-by: Daniel Micay <danielmicay@gmail.com>
---
 lib/nlattr.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/lib/nlattr.c b/lib/nlattr.c
index bc5b5cf608c4..5cc8edbbfb5c 100644
--- a/lib/nlattr.c
+++ b/lib/nlattr.c
@@ -723,6 +723,8 @@ int nla_memcpy(void *dest, const struct nlattr *src, int count)
 {
 	int minlen = min_t(int, count, nla_len(src));
 
+	BUG_ON(minlen < 0);
+
 	memcpy(dest, nla_data(src), minlen);
 	if (count > minlen)
 		memset(dest + minlen, 0, count - minlen);
